\ Pairs, wide: many pairs under GC churn, mixed aggregates, reachability.
\ Pairs live in a GC'd table; these check survival, reclamation, and that the
\ collector reaches pairs through arrays, through other pairs, and through
\ logic-variable bindings.

\ a kept pair survives heavy pair churn plus a collection
variable KEEP
[( 7 8 9 null )] to KEEP
[: |> i | [( i i 1+ null )] drop :] 200000 i-times
gc
KEEP . cr                                          \ [( 7 8 9 null )]

\ a pair reachable only through a logic-variable binding survives GC
variable V
lvar to V
V [( 1 2 null )] ~ drop
gc
V . cr                                             \ [( 1 2 null )]

\ a list whose elements are themselves lists
[( [( 1 null )] [( 2 null )] [( 3 null )] null )] . cr

\ pairs inside an array survive GC (mark reaches in through the array)
[ [( 1 2 null )] [( 3 4 null )] ] gc . cr          \ [ [( 1 2 null )] [( 3 4 null )] ]

\ arrays inside a pair survive GC (mark reaches in through the pair)
[( [ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] null )] gc . cr                 \ [( [ 1 2 ] [ 3 4 ] null )]

\ many distinct lists held in an array all survive
[ [( 1 null )] [( 2 null )] [( 3 null )] [( 4 null )] [( 5 null )] ] gc . cr

bye
